## SPRITE SYSTEM (SpriteManager.kt + vector drawables)

Draw ALL sprites as Vector Drawable XML files.
Each sprite must match the NES Duck Hunt pixel art style:
- Bold outlines
- Flat colors, no gradients inside sprites
- Chunky pixel-art proportions

### Duck sprite (ic_duck_fly_1/2/3.xml):
3-frame wing flap animation. Duck body = brown oval, wing = darker brown 
rectangle that rotates -30°/0°/+30° between frames. Head = small circle 
with orange beak. White chest patch. Green head on mallard variant.
Size: 48x40dp in vector viewBox.

### Duck animation states:
- FLYING: cycle frames 1→2→3→2→1 every 120ms
- HIT_FLASH: alternate white fill / normal fill 3 times over 300ms
- FALLING: use ic_duck_fall.xml — duck rotated 90° with X eyes, falls straight down
- ESCAPED: use ic_duck_escape.xml — duck flies straight up off screen

### Plate sprite:
ic_plate_1.xml: orange-brown circle (clay pigeon), diameter 32dp
ic_plate_break_1.xml and ic_plate_break_2.xml: two half-circle shards 
that fly apart in opposite directions when shot

### Crosshair (ic_crosshair.xml):
Classic duck hunt crosshair: outer circle, inner dot, four perpendicular 
lines. Color: white with dark outline. Size 64x64dp.
Rendered LAST (on top of everything).

### Dog sprites:
ic_dog_sniff.xml: beagle dog, low to ground, nose forward (intro animation)
ic_dog_carry.xml: dog jumping up holding duck in mouth (successful round)
ic_dog_laugh.xml: dog peering over grass laughing (missed all ducks)
These appear in the grass strip area only.

