## GAME MECHANICS — EXACT DUCK HUNT RULES

### Crosshair Control:
- User DRAGS finger anywhere on screen to move the crosshair
- Crosshair follows finger 1:1 — no acceleration, no lag
- Crosshair clamped to screen bounds minus 32dp padding
- When finger lifts: SHOOT action fires at current crosshair position
- Crosshair can be moved WHILE finger is held — lift = shoot
- Gun sprite at bottom of screen rotates to point toward current crosshair position
  Use: angle = atan2(crosshairY - gunY, crosshairX - gunX) converted to degrees
  Apply rotation to gun drawable using canvas.rotate()

### Gun (GunRenderer.kt + Gun.kt):
- Drawn at bottom-center of screen, above HUD
- Width: 80dp, positioned at (screenWidth/2, screenHeight - 120dp)
- Rotates smoothly toward crosshair using angle lerp: 
  currentAngle += (targetAngle - currentAngle) * 0.25f each frame
- On SHOOT: gun recoil animation — translate gun backward 8dp over 80ms, 
  return over 120ms
- Muzzle flash: white circle at gun barrel tip, visible for 2 frames (33ms)

### Shooting Logic:
- User has exactly 3 shots per round (shown as bullet icons in HUD)
- On finger lift → decrement ammo → check hit detection → play sound + vibrate
- Hit detection: circle collision — if crosshair center is within 
  (duck/plate radius + 20dp) → HIT
- The 20dp bonus makes it feel fair like the original light gun
- On HIT: target enters HIT_FLASH state → then FALLING state → 
  dog carries it → score added
- On MISS: bullet deducted, no target reaction
- If all 3 shots used and targets remain → targets ESCAPE 
  (fly off top of screen) → dog laughs

### Round Structure (LevelManager.kt):
Each level = one round. Within a level:
- DUCK MODE: 2 ducks fly simultaneously (levels 1-5), or 1 duck (tutorial/easy)
- PLATE MODE: every 3rd level → throw clay plates instead of ducks
- Round starts → dog jumps in grass (1.5s animation) → ducks/plates launch

### Duck flight path (Duck.kt):
- Ducks enter from a random edge (left or right of screen, or bottom-left/right)
- Fly in a zigzag arc path: primary direction + perpendicular sine wave
- Path is defined by: startPos, primaryVelocity, sineAmplitude, sineFrequency
- Speed increases each level: baseSpeed = 120dp/s + (level * 15dp/s), capped at 400dp/s
- If duck reaches top of screen without being shot → ESCAPED
- Ducks never fly off left/right edges — they bounce off screen sides

### Plate flight path (Plate.kt):
- Plate launches from bottom-left or bottom-right corner
- Follows a parabolic arc (projectile physics): 
  vx = constant, vy = initial upward - gravity accumulation each frame
- Plate rotates continuously during flight (visualRotation += 8f per frame)
- Plate explodes into two shards when hit
- Shards fly apart with opposite velocities and fade out over 400ms

