## SOUND SYSTEM (SoundSynthesizer.kt + SoundManager.kt)

Generate ALL sounds programmatically using AudioTrack. 
No external audio files needed.

### SoundId.kt:
```kotlin
enum class SoundId {
    GUNSHOT,
    DUCK_QUACK,
    DUCK_FALL,
    DUCK_ESCAPED,
    DOG_LAUGH,
    DOG_BARK,
    PLATE_LAUNCH,
    PLATE_BREAK,
    ROUND_START,
    LEVEL_CLEAR,
    GAME_OVER,
    MENU_SELECT,
    SCORE_TICK,
    PERFECT_ROUND
}
```

### SoundSynthesizer.kt — generate each sound:

GUNSHOT: 
Sharp noise burst. White noise at full amplitude for 15ms, 
then exponential decay to silence over 120ms.
Add low-frequency thump: sine wave at 80Hz, 60ms, fast decay.
Mix together: 60% noise + 40% thump.

DUCK_QUACK:
Two-tone warble. Alternate between 400Hz and 500Hz sine wave, 
switching every 40ms, total 200ms. Apply slight vibrato (±20Hz at 8Hz rate).
Amplitude envelope: quick attack 10ms, sustain, quick decay 30ms.

DUCK_FALL:
Descending whistle. Sine wave from 800Hz → 200Hz over 600ms.
Add slight wobble (±30Hz sine modulation at 12Hz).

DUCK_ESCAPED:
Ascending whistle. Sine wave from 300Hz → 1200Hz over 400ms. 
Fade out over last 100ms.

DOG_LAUGH:
Three short "heh" sounds. Each: burst of 300Hz sine, 80ms, 
with sharp attack and decay. Gap of 100ms between each.

DOG_BARK:
Noise burst 30ms + 180Hz sine 80ms. Quick and punchy.

PLATE_LAUNCH:
Rising whoosh. Noise filtered to low frequencies, 
amplitude ramps up from 0 to peak over 200ms.

PLATE_BREAK:
Short crack. High-frequency noise (5kHz region) burst 25ms + 
noise decay 80ms. Sounds like ceramic breaking.

ROUND_START:
Simple 3-note ascending arpeggio: 262Hz, 330Hz, 392Hz (C-E-G).
Each note 150ms, sine wave, slight fade out at end of each.

LEVEL_CLEAR:
5-note ascending melody: 262, 294, 330, 349, 392 Hz.
Each note 120ms, square wave (more NES-sounding):
square wave = if (sin(angle) > 0) amplitude else -amplitude

GAME_OVER:
Descending 4-note phrase: 392, 330, 294, 262 Hz.
Each 180ms, square wave, slight echo effect 
(add delayed copy at 30% amplitude after 120ms).

PERFECT_ROUND:
Jingle: 523, 659, 784, 1047 Hz, each 100ms, sine wave.
Followed by a trill between 784 and 880 Hz alternating every 30ms for 300ms.

SCORE_TICK:
Very short tick: 800Hz sine, 20ms, full amplitude then instant cut.

MENU_SELECT:
Short blip: 440Hz sine, 40ms, quick fade.

### SoundManager.kt:
- Pre-generate all sounds on app start using coroutines (IO dispatcher)
- Store as ShortArray in memory map: Map<SoundId, ShortArray>
- Playback: for each play() call, submit to a single-thread executor
  that creates an AudioTrack, writes the ShortArray, plays, releases
- Max 4 simultaneous sounds (use 4 AudioTrack instances in a pool)
- Volume control: master volume Float, applied per sound
- SoundManager is a singleton injected via Koin

