## GAME FLOW IMPLEMENTATION

### GameEngine.kt:
States (sealed class):
- Idle
- DogIntro (dog sniff animation, 1.5s)
- DuckLaunch (ducks appear from grass)
- Playing (active gameplay)
- RoundResult (show hits/misses, dog reaction, 2.5s)
- LevelClear (level complete celebration)
- GameOver

State machine transitions:
Idle → DogIntro → DuckLaunch → Playing → RoundResult → 
  if rounds_left > 0: DuckLaunch
  else if passed: LevelClear → next level → DogIntro
  else: GameOver

### GameLoop.kt:
- Fixed timestep: 16.67ms (60 FPS)
- Thread-based loop on dedicated HandlerThread
- Canvas locked in SurfaceHolder.lockHardwareCanvas() / unlockCanvasAndPost()
- Delta time capped at 50ms
- update(dt) → render() each frame
- Thread stops cleanly on surfaceDestroyed()

### Touch handling (GameSurfaceView.kt):
```kotlin
override fun onTouchEvent(event: MotionEvent): Boolean {
    when (event.actionMasked) {
        MotionEvent.ACTION_DOWN, MotionEvent.ACTION_MOVE -> {
            // Update crosshair position — track finger 1:1
            gameEngine.updateCrosshair(event.x, event.y)
        }
        MotionEvent.ACTION_UP -> {
            // Finger lifted = SHOOT at current crosshair position
            gameEngine.shoot(event.x, event.y)
        }
    }
    return true
}
```

