## LAN MULTIPLAYER

### How it works:
Same-WiFi competitive play. Each player plays their own game.
Live scores shown in overlay. Highest score at end wins.

### LanDiscovery.kt:
- UDP multicast group: 239.255.12.99 port 47777
- Heartbeat every 1s: JSON {"action":"HELLO","name":"PlayerName","ip":"...","profileId":"..."}
- Evict players not seen in 5s
- Acquire WifiManager.MulticastLock before joining group
- Release lock in onDestroy

### MultiplayerMessage.kt (kotlinx.serialization):
```kotlin
@Serializable
sealed class MultiplayerMessage {
    @Serializable data class Hello(val name: String, val profileId: Long, val ip: String) : MultiplayerMessage()
    @Serializable data class StartGame(val seed: Long) : MultiplayerMessage()  // same seed = same duck patterns
    @Serializable data class ScoreUpdate(val profileId: Long, val score: Long, val level: Int, val isAlive: Boolean) : MultiplayerMessage()
    @Serializable data class GameEnd(val profileId: Long, val finalScore: Long) : MultiplayerMessage()
}
```

