## ANIMATION SEQUENCES

### Dog Intro Sequence (DogIntro state, 1.5s):
0ms: dog sprite appears running from left edge at grass level
400ms: dog stops at center, sniffs ground (ic_dog_sniff.xml)
800ms: dog jumps straight up (translate Y upward 40dp over 200ms)
1000ms: dog disappears below grass (translate Y down off screen)
1200ms: ducks launch

### Dog Success Sequence (hit all ducks, 2s):
Dog jumps up from grass holding duck (ic_dog_carry.xml), 
bounces up 60dp then settles, stays visible 1.5s, 
bark sound plays, drops back down.

### Dog Laugh Sequence (missed all ducks, 2.5s):
Dog peeks up from grass (ic_dog_laugh.xml), 
bob up and down slightly,
dog_laugh sound plays,
player CANNOT tap dog (but many will try — add a fun Easter egg: 
if player shoots at dog → dog flinches with a yelp sound and extra 
50 bonus points, screen shows "BAD HUNTER! +50")

### Duck Hit Sequence:
Frame 0: HIT detected
Frames 1-6: duck flashes white (alternate fill colors every 2 frames, 100ms total)
Frame 7: duck switches to ic_duck_fall.xml
Frames 8-40: duck falls straight down, slight rotation
When duck exits bottom of screen: dog carry sequence begins
Score number pops up at duck's last position, floats upward, fades out (1s)

### Duck Escape Sequence:
All shots used, duck still alive:
Duck immediately changes direction to fly straight up
Speed doubles
duck_escaped sound plays
Duck exits top of screen
If BOTH ducks escape → dog laughs

